Version: 0.1.9
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Security hardening for generated-map bootstrap git calls:
  replaced shell-string `execSync` invocation with argument-array
  `execFileSync('git', [...])`, eliminating shell interpolation risk
  from crafted directory names.
- Cross-platform path handling fix in bootstrap target expansion:
  replaced slash-based basename extraction with `path.basename`,
  so second-level scope discovery works correctly on Windows paths.
- Runtime false-start nudge precision fix:
  removed overly broad concrete-output heuristics that treated inline
  code/path mentions as execution evidence, restoring nudge behavior
  when the assistant promises actions without tool calls.
- Regression coverage:
  added tests to verify bootstrap does not execute shell substitutions
  from directory names and that path/code mentions still trigger
  false-start nudge when no actual execution evidence exists.

Related commits:
- fix(bootstrap): secure git invocation + path basename compatibility
- fix(loop): avoid false negatives in shouldNudge with path/code mentions
